description._content: Description: Portion of 2000 native carriers waiting while S.A.M.R. Guns are in action. Note herd of 3/400 cattle just captured from enemy. Description: First jetties ever made on Lake Nyasa. (M'Bamba ). Location: M'bamba Description: S.A.M.R. Guns in action near Iringa. Location: Iringa Description: View at "Old Langenberg" on the Lake. N.B.This is the outlet for the Tandala Plateau Location: Tandala Description: Self returning off column from Iringa. Location: Iringa Description: Head Quarters car on the Ssongra-Liwale Road, Showing class of bridge built by South African Engineers. Location: Ssongra, Liwale Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/133 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives, uploaded as part of the Africa Through a Lens project. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons. Our records about many of these images are limited.
